{PKG} {VER}
A small CLI tool to detect CPU flags (instruction sets) of X86 binaries.

Usage:

    $ {BIN_NAME} [<option>...] <file>

Options:

      --mode <mode>       select mode of operation: detect, stats, details
  -s, --stats             alias for '--mode stats'
  -d, --details           alias for '--mode details'

      --output <level>    select output level: normal, quiet, verbose
  -q, --quiet             alias for '--output quiet'
  -v, --verbose           alias for '--output verbose'

  -h, --help              display this message and exit
      --                  stop reading any options and treat the next argument as a file path
